<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,546,1061]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,327,586,612]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
First sector of m-cu longer than in other genera of subfamily, m-cu reaching CuA more distally. M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[242,267,642,656]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">1+2</subScript>
/M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[301,325,642,656]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">3+4</subScript>
shorter than m-cu, r-m long. Tergites 1-4 and 6 shining brown, tergite 5 yellow. Midpleural pit absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1316,709,735]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,546,1061]" box="[199,1316,709,735]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,339,709,735]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is feminine, from the Greek 
<emphasis box="[894,967,710,735]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">eratos</emphasis>
, lovely, meaning a lovely fly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,546,1061]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,341,749,775]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Comments.</emphasis>
This genus, which is known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[854,904,749,775]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">type</typeStatus>
species, from 
<collectingCountry box="[1077,1176,749,775]" name="Ecuador" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, appears in the phylogenetic analysis (below) as the sister group of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chandler" authorityYear="2002" box="[708,841,790,815]" class="Insecta" family="Rangomaramidae" genus="Chiletricha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[708,841,790,815]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Chiletricha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is known from 
<collectingCountry box="[1122,1188,789,815]" name="Chile" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Chile</collectingCountry>
, southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1312,1432,789,815]" name="Argentina" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, and southern 
<collectingCountry box="[310,385,829,855]" name="Brazil" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. It differs from the 
<taxonomicName box="[615,841,829,855]" class="Insecta" family="Rangomaramidae" genus="Chiletricha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[615,748,830,855]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Chiletricha</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in wing features, with a much wider basal cell, R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1428,1436,845,859]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">5</subScript>
separated from C, and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[440,448,888,902]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">4</subScript>
originating from CuA not as basally in the wing (
<figureCitation box="[1026,1124,872,898]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–10" captionStartId="55.[151,269,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[201,1398,194,1934]" captionTargetId="figure-44@55.[201,1399,194,1940]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="FIGURES 7–10. Eratomyia magnifica, sp. n. 7. Head (apical maxillary palpal segments not represented), lateral view. 8. Thorax. 9. Front tibial apex, inner view. 10. Wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5088521" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5088521/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Figs. 10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1136,1168,872,898]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19" captionStartId="57.[151,269,1915,1939]" captionTargetBox="[179,1398,194,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-44@57.[179,1398,194,1889]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. Chiletricha. 16, 17. Chiletricha seminuda (Freeman). 16. Wing. 17. Mouthparts, posterior view. 18, 19. Chiletricha marginata (Edwards). 18. Thorax. 19. Male terminalia, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5088527" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5088527/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">16</figureCitation>
). Mouthparts are fairly similar (
<figureCitation box="[248,332,915,941]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–10" captionStartId="55.[151,269,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[201,1398,194,1934]" captionTargetId="figure-44@55.[201,1399,194,1940]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="FIGURES 7–10. Eratomyia magnifica, sp. n. 7. Head (apical maxillary palpal segments not represented), lateral view. 8. Thorax. 9. Front tibial apex, inner view. 10. Wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5088521" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5088521/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Figs. 7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[344,376,915,941]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19" captionStartId="57.[151,269,1915,1939]" captionTargetBox="[179,1398,194,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-44@57.[179,1398,194,1889]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. Chiletricha. 16, 17. Chiletricha seminuda (Freeman). 16. Wing. 17. Mouthparts, posterior view. 18, 19. Chiletricha marginata (Edwards). 18. Thorax. 19. Male terminalia, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5088527" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5088527/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">17</figureCitation>
). In the thorax, the mesepimeron of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Published" authorityYear="2007" box="[802,926,915,940]" class="Insecta" family="Rangomaramidae" genus="Eratomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[802,926,915,940]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Eratomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is more slender on its ventral half, whereas the laterotergite is slightly larger (
<figureCitation box="[551,634,955,981]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–10" captionStartId="55.[151,269,1954,1978]" captionTargetBox="[201,1398,194,1934]" captionTargetId="figure-44@55.[201,1399,194,1940]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="FIGURES 7–10. Eratomyia magnifica, sp. n. 7. Head (apical maxillary palpal segments not represented), lateral view. 8. Thorax. 9. Front tibial apex, inner view. 10. Wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5088521" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5088521/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Figs. 8</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[649,681,955,981]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19" captionStartId="57.[151,269,1915,1939]" captionTargetBox="[179,1398,194,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-44@57.[179,1398,194,1889]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. Chiletricha. 16, 17. Chiletricha seminuda (Freeman). 16. Wing. 17. Mouthparts, posterior view. 18, 19. Chiletricha marginata (Edwards). 18. Thorax. 19. Male terminalia, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5088527" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5088527/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">18</figureCitation>
). Tergite 9 has strong spines on a pair of distal projections (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 11–15" captionStartId="56.[151,269,1977,2001]" captionTargetBox="[215,1370,182,1963]" captionTargetId="figure-52@56.[214,1374,182,1963]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURES 11–15. Eratomyia magnifica, sp. n. 11. Male terminalia, posterior view. 12. Male terminalia, lateral view. 13. Gonostyle, external view. 14. Aedeagus and gonocoxal bridge. 15. Tergites VIII–X and cerci, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5088523" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5088523/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 12–15</figureCitation>
), as also seen in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chandler" authorityYear="2002" box="[444,577,995,1020]" class="Insecta" family="Rangomaramidae" genus="Chiletricha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[444,577,995,1020]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Chiletricha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[597,688,995,1021]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–19" captionStartId="57.[151,269,1915,1939]" captionTargetBox="[179,1398,194,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-44@57.[179,1398,194,1889]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURES 16–19. Chiletricha. 16, 17. Chiletricha seminuda (Freeman). 16. Wing. 17. Mouthparts, posterior view. 18, 19. Chiletricha marginata (Edwards). 18. Thorax. 19. Male terminalia, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5088527" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5088527/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[714,960,995,1020]" class="Insecta" family="Rangomaramidae" genus="Rhynchoheterotricha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[714,960,995,1020]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Rhynchoheterotricha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jaschhof" authorityYear="2004" box="[1032,1175,995,1020]" class="Insecta" family="Rangomaramidae" genus="Insulatricha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1032,1175,995,1020]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Insulatricha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the gonocoxites have a pair of unique digitiform projections bearing setae and a pair of spines.
</paragraph>
